Rite Aid was founded in 1962 as the Thrif D Discount Center, and has grown to become the largest drugstore chain on the East Coast and the third largest drugstore chain in the US. Its retail stores provide pharmacy services… MoreRite Aid was founded in 1962 as the Thrif D Discount Center, and has grown to become the largest drugstore chain on the East Coast and the third largest drugstore chain in the US. Its retail stores provide pharmacy services and sell prescription drugs and front-end products.

On June 29, 2017, Rite Aid entered into an agreement with Walgreens Boots Alliance (WBA) to sell 2,186 Rite Aid Stores and related assets for $5.175 Billion. The transaction is expected to close within six months but is subject to antitrust clearance. The 2,186 stores included in the agreement are primarily located in the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic and Southeastern regions of the United States. The three distribution centers included in the agreement are located in Dayville, Conn., Philadelphia and Spartanburg, S.C. The company also announced the termination of the agreement, announced on October 27, 2015 under which WBA would have acquired all outstanding shares of Rite Aid on account of not receiving regulatory approval.   

Rite Aid acquired EnvisionRX in 2015.
IT Priorities:
•Rite Aid corporation is considering a move onto virtual desktop infrastructure (VDI), and is managing an ongoing server virtualization effort.
•The company has begun a move onto cloud computing, and cost is the primary concern for all future cloud projects.
•The… MoreIT Priorities:
•Rite Aid corporation is considering a move onto virtual desktop infrastructure (VDI), and is managing an ongoing server virtualization effort.
•The company has begun a move onto cloud computing, and cost is the primary concern for all future cloud projects.
•The company maintains a consistent focus on data analysis, point of sales systems (POS), and telemedicine services, largely managed by the Pharmacy and Store Systems groups.
•The IT department is working to maintain its current systems, pending the enterprise roll out of an up to date Windows OS in 2014.
•Rite Aid is nearing the completion of a bring your own device (BYOD) platform to its retail stores.  The project began in 2012 with an implementation for corporate employees.

IT Structure:
•Personnel working in the Supply Chain group handle IT procurement and vendor relations. All of Rite Aid's possible vendors must be authorized through the Vendor Management Office, which can be contacted at vendormgmt@riteaid.com.
•The IT department's staff is spread across three locations in Pennsylvania: Etters, Shiremans Town, and the headquarters in Camp Hill.

IT Intelligence:
2013:
•The company completed an Avaya VoIP implementation project that began in 2012.
•The Rite Aid network environment is primarily run on Cisco and Nortel equipment.

2012:
•Rite Aid selected WorkPlace OnLine, a schedule and attendance cloud-based platform from WorkPlace Systems Inc. that will be utilized within the company's pharmacy division.





